AUDIO: 'the Ivy League school\'s personally enriching coursework with minimal effort. When asked why he had gone through so much trouble to get to an Ivy League university only to offload all of the learning to a robot, he told'

[02:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'reporter James D. Walsh, quote, "It\'s the best place to meet your co-founder and your wife." While his chat GPT bot continued to achieve his high grades for him, the young man without a chest was'

[02:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'hardly idle. As an aspiring computer coder, he\'d spent over 600 soul crushing hours grinding through Elite Code, a platform meant to prep students for the technical interviews at big tech'

[03:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'companies. Lee and just about every other kid he knew thought it was pointless. So Lee flipped the script. What if you didn\'t solve the riddles yourself? What if just like a research paper for a history class, AI could do'

[03:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it for you and remain undetectable even during remote interviews? So that\'s exactly what he and his partner Neil Shanmam built. In February 2025, they launched Interview Coder, a tool that'

[03:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quietly ran AI in the background to help users cheat in live coding interviews. One month later, Colombia called him into the academic integrity office. the verdict guilty of promoting a cheating'

[03:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tool and showing others how to use it. Lee was slapped with disciplinary probation. But here\'s the twist. Lee didn\'t think he\'d done anything wrong. In fact, he argues that interview coder'

