AUDIO: 'school admits it or not. For Lee and his peers, it\'s not even cheating. AI is just the new normal. To give you a sense of just how normal, here are some stats. According to Walsh, in January 2023,'

[04:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just 2 months after OpenAI launched Chat GPT, a survey of 1,000 college students found that nearly 90% of them had used Chatbot to help with homework'

[04:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'assignments. Two and a half years later, students at large state schools, the IVS, liberal arts schools in New England, universities abroad, professional schools, community colleges are all relying on AI to ease their way'

[05:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'through every facet of their education. Generative AI chat bots, Chat GPT, but now also Google\'s Gemini, Anthropics Claude, Microsoft\'s Copilot, and others. They take their notes during class for'

[05:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'them, devise their study guides for them and their practice tests, summarize novels and textbooks, brainstorm, outline, draft the essays. 90% of STEM students are using AI to automate their research and data analyses, and to sail'

[05:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'through dense coding and debugging assignments. Well, what about the professors? Surely the experts in the field with their degrees from Ivy League schools and their host of peer-reviewed studies will be able to distinguish'

[05:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'human from AI work, right? No. A June 2024 study in the UK found that professors missed 97% of AI generated essays in their own fields of expertise. Even AI powered AI'

[06:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'detectors can\'t discern human from computer work. To that point, Walsh fed quote a chunk of the book of Genesis into AI detector zero GPT and it told him the chapter was'

[06:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '93.33% AI generated. That\'s right, the Bible is 93% written by chatbots. The reality is AI is here and no one can keep up and it goes way beyond'

[06:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'universities. Tyler Cohen reported recently in the Free Press, "In 2019, GPT2 could barely count to five or string together coherent sentences. By 2023, GPT4 was outperforming nearly 90% of human test'

[06:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'takers on medical licensing exams and the bar exam. In 2024, Claude 3.5 sonnet was answering questions about complex scientific diagrams and charts with over'

[06:55] [scene:talk]
